               <p>SARAH DENBY. I am the wife of Samuel Denby. The prisoner had a furnished room in our house - I missed the articles stated, and had him taken on the 15th of April; I had let these articles to the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-315-person2646">
                  JOSEPH 
                  BEAL
               <interp inst="t18300415-315-person2646" type="surname" value="BEAL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-315-person2646" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-315-person2646" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I was sent for and took the prisoner - I found four duplicates of the articles, which were pawned; they were in a drawer, and he gave them to me.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-315-person2647">
                  HENRY 
                  ROBERT REDWOOD
               <interp inst="t18300415-315-person2647" type="surname" value="ROBERT REDWOOD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-315-person2647" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-315-person2647" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am in the service of a pawnbroker - I gave these two duplicates to a person who pawned this blanket and pillow; these other two were written by a young man in our service.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. They would have been redeemed on the Saturday following - I had a job, and wanted 5s. worth of varnish.</p>
               <p>
